T1

xn>1⇒1<xn+1=3xn+1xn+3<3Inductively,xn∈(1,3)xn+1−xn=3xn+1−xn2−3xnxn+3=1−xn2xn+3<0∴{xn}is bounded and decreasinglimn→∞xnexists.xn+1=3xn+1xn+3⇒limn→∞xn=3(limn→∞xn)+1(limn→∞xn)+3⇒limn→∞xn=1

∀n,an<bn⇒{bn>an+1=anbn>anan<bn+1=an+bn2<bn⇒{an<bn<bn−1<…<b1,bn>an>an−1>…>a1⇒{an},{bn} is bounded and monotonic⇒A=limn→∞an,B=limn→∞bn exists⇒{limn→∞bn+1=limn→∞an+bn2limn→∞an+1=anbn⇒{B=A+B2A=AB⇒A=B

T3

设数列 {xn} 满足 0<xn<1 与 (1−xn)xn+1>14,n=1,2,3,…, 求证: limn→∞xn=12.

14(1−xn)<xn+1<1⇒xn<3414(1−xn−1)<xn<34⇒xn−1<23同理⇒xn−2<12∴∀n,xn<12又xn+1=14(1−xn)>xn⇔(2xn−1)2>0⇒TrueX=limn→∞xn existsxn+1>14(1−xn)⇒X≥14(1−X)⇒X=12

T4

设 x1∈(0,1),xn+1=xn(1−xn),n∈N+, 证明: 数列 {nxn} 收敛, 并求其极限.

limn→∞1xnn⟸ Stolz Theorem limn→∞1xn−1xn−1=limn→∞1xn−1(1−xn−1)−1xn−1=limn→∞11−xn−1=11−limn→∞xn−1

x1≤11,x2<min(x1,1−x1)≤12xn≤1n,n≥2⇒xn+1<1n(1−1n)=n−1n2<1n+1}⇒xn≤1n0<xn≤1n⟹Squeeze Theoremlimn→∞xn=0⇒limn→∞1xnn=11−limn→∞xn=1⇒limn→∞nxn=1

T5

求极限 limn→∞(n!e−[n!e]).

an=n!e−[n!e]=limn→∞{n!e}=limn→∞{∑i=0∞n!i!}=limn→∞{∑i=n+1∞n!i!}=limn→∞{1n+1+1(n+1)(n+2)+1(n+1)(n+2)(n+3)+…}<limn→∞{∑i=1∞(n+1)−i}=limn→∞{1n}=0

T6

求极限 limn→∞an(1n+1+1n+2+⋯+1n+n).

x>ln⁡(x)+1⇒1x∈(ln⁡(xx−1),ln⁡(x+1x))⇒an∈(∑i=n+12nln⁡(ii−1),∑i=n+12nln⁡(i+1i))=(ln⁡(2nn),ln⁡(2n+1n+1))⟹Squeeze Theoremlimn→∞an=ln⁡(2)

Class 6

T1

A,Bis upper bounder,S⊂{x+y|x∈A,y∈B}⇒supS≤supA+supB

显然S有界,则supS存在.

若supS>supA+supB,取M=supA+supB,

则∀x∈A,y∈B,x≤supA,y≤supB⇒x+y≤M

于是M是比supS小的上界,矛盾.

故supS≤supA+supB

eg. 当A,B,S均为有限集恰好为 ${ x+y\vert x\in A,y\in B } $ 时显然严格不等号不成立.

T2

A,B aren’t empty,α≥0,C=A+αB={x|x=a+αb,a∈A,b∈B}}⇒sup(A+αB)=M=supA+αsupB
∀c∈C=a+αb,a≤supA,b≤supB⇒a+αb≤supA+αsupB=M∀M′<M,ϵ=M−M′let X=supA−ϵ3,Y=supB+ϵ3αAccording to the definition of supremum, ∃a>X∈A,y>Y∈B⇒∃c=a+b∈C,c>X+Y>M′⇒supC=supA+αsupB

T3

A⊂B⇒supA≤supB,infA≥infB
if supA>supBlet M=supB⟹Def of supremum∃a∈A,a>M=supBa∈A⟹A⊂Ba∈Ba>supB}⇒False∴supA≤supB

取 C=−A,D=−B,C⊂D,supC≤supD⇒infA≥infB,

T4

∀x∈A,y∈B,x≤y⇒supA≤infB

假设supA>infB,M∈(supA,infB),由supA定义∃a∈A,a>M,由infB定义∃b∈B,b<M,故a>M>b,与∀x∈A,y∈B,x≤y矛盾.

故supA≤infB
